result.adr_address: 13 King Kwong St, Happy Valley, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 13 King Kwong St, Happy Valley, Hong Kong
result.name: Zagin Soba

reviews.text:
Delicious creamy frothy broth, although a bit on the salty side. Service here is excellent!
138 for creamy frothy chicken ramen + 15 for the egg

It’s my 3rd time visiting Zagin Soba on gough street, I like their soup base and the texture of the noodles, however the fried chicken we ordered was a bit too dried. It was a pleasant experience overall. A bone to pick is that, they have very bad Wi-Fi reception inside the restaurant.

Great texture tsekemen and nice soup base, rich flavour. The price is a bit high though. 

And it's a very considerate shop that one-time toothbrush and mouth wash are provided which help you to keep refreshed after the meal
The best ramen in town.  Very rich in flavor and love the texture of the noodle!
Good services and environment.  But the food is a bit salty.
